<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8" standalone="yes"?>
<bug>
    <id>226732</id>
    <title>add bookmark dialog doesn't close after bookmark added</title>
    <description>
        <paragraph id="1">
            <sentence id="1.1">User-Agent:       Mozilla/5.0 (Macintosh; U; PPC Mac OS X Mach-O; en-US; rv:1.6b) Gecko/20031124 Firebird/0.7+
Build Identifier: Mozilla/5.0 (Macintosh; U; PPC Mac OS X Mach-O; en-US; rv:1.6b) Gecko/20031124 Firebird/0.7+</sentence>
        </paragraph>
        <paragraph id="2">
            <sentence id="2.1">The add bookmark dialog doesn't close after the OK button is pressed.</sentence>
            <sentence id="2.2">It gives
no indication whatsoever that it's done anything.</sentence>
            <sentence id="2.3">The only way to get rid of it
is to press cancel.</sentence>
        </paragraph>
        <paragraph id="3">
            <sentence id="3.1">I suppose you could argue this is a feature supporting the really important
requirement to add the same bookmark in multiple places in the bookmark menu.</sentence>
        </paragraph>
        <paragraph id="4">
            <sentence id="4.1">Reproducible: Always</sentence>
        </paragraph>
        <paragraph id="5">
            <sentence id="5.1">Steps to Reproduce:</sentence>
            <sentence id="5.2">1 visit some page</sentence>
            <sentence id="5.3">2 select Bookmarks-&gt;Add to Bookmarks from the menu bar</sentence>
            <sentence id="5.4">3 click OK on the resulting dialog box</sentence>
        </paragraph>
        <paragraph id="6">
            <sentence id="6.1">Actual Results:  
Nothing happens visually, though the bookmark is added.</sentence>
            <sentence id="6.2">The dialog box stays up.</sentence>
        </paragraph>
        <paragraph id="7">
            <sentence id="7.1">Expected Results:  
Taken away the dialog box, or at least give some indication the bookmark has
been added.</sentence>
        </paragraph>
    </description>
</bug>
